✨ Features
✅ User-Friendly Web Interface (Streamlit)
✅ Real-Time Loan Eligibility Prediction
✅ Machine Learning Model (Random Forest Classifier)
✅ Responsive & Clean UI
✅ Confidence Score for Decisions

🛠 Tech Stack
Python

Streamlit (Web App)

Scikit-learn (ML Model)

Pandas & NumPy (Data Processing)

Joblib (Model Saving/Loading)

⚙ Installation
1. Clone the Repository
bash
git clone https://github.com/KanchanDhanik/ML-Projects-Tamizhan-Skills/tree/main/LoanEligibilityPredictor
cd LoanEligibilityPredictor
2. Install Dependencies
bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Run the App
bash
streamlit run app.py
App will open at: http://localhost:8501

🚀 Usage
Fill in the applicant details:

Personal Info (Gender, Education, Employment Status)

Financial Info (Income, Loan Amount, Credit History)

Click "Predict Loan Eligibility"

Get instant approval/rejection with confidence score!

📊 Dataset
The model is trained on a loan prediction dataset containing:

Features:

Gender, Married, Dependents, Education, Self_Employed

ApplicantIncome, CoapplicantIncome, LoanAmount, Credit_History

Target Variable: Loan_Status (Y/N)

Dataset Source: Kaggle Loan Prediction Dataset

🤖 Model Training
Algorithm: Random Forest Classifier (~76% Accuracy)

Preprocessing Steps:

Handling missing values

Encoding categorical features

Scaling numerical data

Model Saved As: loan_model.pkl

To retrain the model:

python
from loan_model import LoanEligibilityPredictor
predictor = LoanEligibilityPredictor()
data = predictor.load_data("loan_data.csv")
predictor.train_model(data)
